< review>
Great atmosphere, all of the barbers appeared to be great barbers. I waited a little bit cause I didn't have an appointment so I got to see each one of them cut hair. Every barber there was a perfectionist and took their time with every cut/line. It is definitely recommended to make an appointment with anyone. All the barbers are really good so they all have appointments.

I got my haircut by Willie he's the first chair when you walk in.  He was very polite and a very good barber for someone who just got started. He asked a lot of questions just to make sure I had my hair the way I wanted it.

I also want to mention that these guys still cut my hair even though I was there until after the store closed. They have never seen me because I'm not from around here I just chose this barbershop cause it had great reviews. Some places aren't so welcoming to newcomers and usually don't care for newcomers.

I highly recommend this shop to anyone who is in the area looking for a good cut. I paid the regular price $15. If I could give this place 10 stars I would.< /review>

< review>
This barber shop is all about perfection and customer satisfaction. All barbers are very skilled. My son is mixed with African American so his hair is a bit tricky to cut and style. This place knows exactly what to do when it comes to any type of hair texture. It is always busy because they do an excellent job; however the owner always makes a way to squeeze in all walk-ins. 1426785986816< /date>
<pictures>None<//pictures><Response>None< /Response>< review>
By outside appearance, you might write this place off as some shady hole in the wall, or not even notice it, but that is very deceiving.  The inside is very clean with a masculine, modern style to it and just a tiny hint of 20s vintage.

The location is a reflection of the staff as well.  At first glance you might be temped to write them off as one thing or another, but regardless of what you may take from appearance, they are true professional barbers.  They won't fawn over you, but they are very friendly, welcoming, and able to give you whatever kind of cut you're looking for(and help you find out what that is in my case), all at a good price and a timely manner.

If you're looking for something other than the hospital waiting rooms of more commercial barbers, at a quality and price that beats them. I highly recommend you stop by.< /review>

<Review>We live in an apartment complex nearby and really needed a place for our Golden Retriever to romp, play, and socialize with other dogs and people. We love this park. It's quite large and open with lots of space to run and play. The people have all been very friendly, respectful, and responsible when it comes to their dogs acting out or aggressively. The park is free of trash and people are very good about cleaning up after their animals. If you live nearby and need a place for your dog to socialize and play, you should definitely come out and make some new friends for you and your dog.</Review>< Pictures>

We love going to this dog park. The people are friendly, the dogs are nice (usually), and most dog parents take care of problems as soon as they arise. The only cons to this place is that it has been closed this weekend and the last weekend with no notice or explanation. <Text>Amazing park overall, one of the better ones in Fresno area if your looking for an open, clean, and friendly park. Dogs and owners their are great for the most part, have had a couple incidents, but my 1 year old pit mix absolutely loves this park and running around with all the other dogs. I feel the biggest issue within this park is IGNORANCE on behalf of some of the dog owners. There is a group of ladies that come in the morning with herds of dogs. Of the incidents my boy has had at this park, majority have involved some dog they brought that day. Funny thing is each time something happens and I calm my dog or remove him from the situation they say, "Is this his first time here?" Like they don't remember me, haha I don't like to be rude but I've worked with horses for a couple years and some dog trainers and groomers as well, so i know a fair bit about how to handle an animal. Im no dog expert but i learned a lot from horses and the people i was working with taught me a lot in my time there, so i know this park has an issue with ignorance because there is A LOT of people that come to this dog park and don't realize how to handle a dog, that their dog might very well be the problem, or even how to remove a dog from a tense situation. And overall my boy and me absolutely love this park, its got actual grass EVERYWHERE, some dirt patches, no bark, I've taken my boy to a fair share of parks and this one is towards the top of the list until the owners start interfering. The hardest thing to deal with at this park for me is the the sheer lack of knowledge of how to let a dog be a dog. Don't come to a dog park expecting the dogs to prance side by side the whole time while you walk around, they may get a little rough playing with each other, that does not mean their going to bite each others throats out. O and if you have any type of pitbull, come to this park and be prepared to be looked at a different way. Its the most horrendous, unjust, ignorant, and just flat out rude thing to do, and i wish some people could be educated, but its just impossible i feel. :/< /Text><pictures>None< /pictures><response>None< /response>< gmapID>

<Time>1617060847729< /Time>< text>
Stopped by the Yard House for lunch this day which is located in Westfield mall. First I ordered two tacos, one being the blacked white fish with crema, mango and cabbage, as well as their Korean BBQ short rib taco with green papaya and jicama. ¬†The blackened white fish was really good, with plenty of spice to be satisfying.  Their chicken tortilla soup kept calling out to me before and after the tacos so I ended up ordering it after. ¬†It was rich and creamy, almost like the filling in a pot pie. ¬†The cup is a reasonable size so I left pretty satisfied without feeling stuffed. ¬†Their salad and soup selection looked great so I might be back to try more salad options.< /text>

<user_name>Eric Aufdembrink (AufD)< /user_name><date>1576981027937</date><rating>1<//rating>< review>
My wife took me here after she got a gift card from work. The hostess and both our waitresses were friendly and attentive. I had the bacon cheeseburger while my wife had some kind of chicken sandwich. My wife's sandwich was "okay" according to her. We both had a helping of fries that could only be described as miserly so thanks for helping with my figure I guess. My burger was cooked precisely to rare which is actually how I like it (medium rare requested) but they failed to let it rest so it arrived at the table sopping with juices and strangely lukewarm. Further the house spread for the bun completely overpowered every other taste in the burger. If you can't taste the cheddar on the burger you have a problem. Honestly I hold the manager responsible. He or she is clearly unqualified. I'm embarrassed for whoever let such a sloppy excuse for an American classic exit their kitchen.<//review>

<rate>5</rate><Resp>None< /Resp>< review>
I always go to the Yard House during Happy Hour because they have one of the best. I'm not a big drinker, but half priced appetizers and pizzas will always keep me coming back for more. The Poke Nachos are my favorite and I still don't know how they pack so much flavor in them.  The pizzas are thin crust and the mozzarella cheese on the Margarita pizza is fresh, stringy when you pull it and delicious. The bar staff is quick to greet you, knowledgeable about the beers and the food, and super friendly.  I always recommend the one at Mission Valley and my wife and I stop there every time we go to the movies.  You will not be disappointed.< /review>

< text>
No wait to be seated on a Monday night, gotta love that. Service was good, price was fair, taste & quality of our food was also good. Do you see anything wrong with my picture? I could tell that the fries were carefully scattered around the plate to cover the area. I was disappointed in the lack of French fries, but I did not feel like complaining & looking petty to the server. I'll just leave my comment here for management. If you're going to be a high-end trendy restaurant, make sure you can afford the fries. I felt like they were just being cheap, trying to make the plate look full. But I'd be happy to go back & give them a chance to redeem themselves. Everything else was good. My sister had fries with her order too, and her serving was also skimpy, so it must be a poor portion size.< /text>

< review>
Honestly this was probably the worst experience I've had a Yard House. The location was pretty empty and our server forgot about us. Appetizers took forever to come out and 1 of the 2 we ordered was forgotten about outright. When we asked our waitress about it, she seemed clueless. We received our food and it was mediocre at best. Though my Mac & Cheese squared, (described as Mac & Cheese on steroids) was pretty underwhelming. The pasta itself seemed very al dente.

The best part of the meal was the beer. The saving grace. The Julian Apple Pie cider was amazing. But it's not made by Yard Horse.

I would go back, but they had better step it up. Evening crew I'm talking about you.< /review>

<Name>Jessica B.< /Name><gmap_id>0x80d95518686323db:0x2f013d9246d12b62</gmap_id><userid>109590001574443470878</userid>< rating>
5</rating>
< Review>
This was my first time at Yardhouse, and I went because I had some gift cards to this restaurant. I went on a Monday night, it wasn't packed, and we were seated right away. They had football playing on the tv, which is nice if you wanna catch the game and grab a bite. We just went on a whim, and lucked out on going during their happy hour. We got half off our appetizers, so we got two instead of one. The best thing was they have vegan/vegetarian friendly option. I got buffalo Gardein wings, which is mock chicken, and it was soo delicious! My bf even liked them, and he's a meat eater. They have a whole section of the menu based on Gardein options. I got the blackened Gardein chicken torta and upgraded to truffle fries. On top of the delicious food, staff was friendly, and made sure we knew all our options on the menu, since it was our first time there. Good place to go with friends with good food. And you can catch a movie after, since AMC is right next door.<//Review>

<userid>109590001574443470878</userid><Name>Jessica B.<//Name><date>1543339473779< /date><Rating>5< /Rating>< text>
This was my first time at Yardhouse, and I went because I had some gift cards to this restaurant. I went on a Monday night, it wasn't packed, and we were seated right away. They had football playing on the tv, which is nice if you wanna catch the game and grab a bite. We just went on a whim, and lucked out on going during their happy hour. We got half off our appetizers, so we got two instead of one. The best thing was they have vegan/vegetarian friendly option. I got buffalo Gardein wings, which is mock chicken, and it was soo delicious! My bf even liked them, and he's a meat eater. They have a whole section of the menu based on Gardein options. I got the blackened Gardein chicken torta and upgraded to truffle fries. On top of the delicious food, staff was friendly, and made sure we knew all our options on the menu, since it was our first time there. Good place to go with friends with good food. And you can catch a movie after, since AMC is right next door.</text>
